## Files to know

- `mkdocs.yml`
  Main documentation site (Marimo-first tutorials and narrative docs).

- `mkdocs-api-ref.yml`
  API reference site (auto-generated).

- `docs_scripts/gen_ref_pages.py`
  Generates API Markdown pages, `SUMMARY.md`, and the `docs/_api_inventory.json` inventory.

- `docs_scripts/api_hooks.py`
  Minimal HTML cleanup and TOC pruning for generated API pages.

- `docs_scripts/main_hooks.py`
  Main docs hook: rewrites `api:` links to point to `/reference/...` URLs. Hard-fails on missing/ambiguous targets.

- `docs_scripts/api_inventory.py`
  Inventory format + progressive qualification resolver used by hooks.

- `serve.py`
  Builds both sites, merges them, and either serves locally or writes to `site/` with `--build-only`. It also cleans up the generated `docs/_api_inventory.json` file after builds.